## Key Concepts

- **LangChain agents and AutoGen-like planners**: Orchestrating multiple AI agents to handle sequential tasks
- **Tool orchestration**: StoryParserAPI, TestCaseAPI, CoverageKB, and CIService working in concert
- **Fault tolerance**: Two-step retries with exponential backoff for resilient execution
- **Performance optimization**: Route-time caching keyed by story ID to eliminate redundant processing
- **Data integrity**: Idempotence checks to prevent duplicate test generation
- **Observability**: Hooks capturing latency, errors, and tool outputs for monitoring

## Code Example

```javascript
const promptTemplate = `Story: {story}\nTask: Parse requirements -> Generate test cases -> Validate coverage -> Execute in CI\n\nPrevious outputs: {context}\n\nCurrent step: {step}\nExecute {tool} and return result.`;

class LangChainAgent {
  async execute(storyId, story) {
    const cache = new Map();
    if (cache.has(storyId)) return cache.get(storyId);

    const tools = [StoryParserAPI, TestCaseAPI, CoverageKB, CIService];
    let context = { storyId, story };

    for (const tool of tools) {
      context = await this.executeWithRetry(tool, context);
    }

    cache.set(storyId, context);
    return context;
  }

  async executeWithRetry(tool, context, attempt = 0) {
    try {
      return await tool.run(context);
    } catch (err) {
      if (attempt < 2) {
        const delay = Math.pow(2, attempt) * 1000;
        await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, delay));
        return this.executeWithRetry(tool, context, attempt + 1);
      }
      throw err;
    }
  }
}

// Observability hooks
agent.on('tool_execute', ({ tool, latency }) => {
  metrics.record('tool_latency', latency, { tool });
});
agent.on('error', ({ tool, error }) => {
  metrics.increment('tool_errors', { tool, error: error.message });
});
```

